The  MercedesBenz Womens Collegiate Championship golf tournament gets

underway this week at the Gettysvue Polo Golf and Country Club in

Knoxville PERIOD Hosted by Tennessee the event will showcase  of the top

collegiate womens golf teams from around the country PERIOD Tee times are at

 a.m PERIOD on Friday and Saturday off the first and tenth holes and an 

a.m PERIOD shotgun start will begin Sundays play PERIOD

The event in entering its third year and will once again feature several of

the nations topranked teams PERIOD Ten of the top  squads in the most recent

MasterCard rankings will hit the par  5985yard Gettysvue layout PERIOD Among

them are Alabama No PERIOD  Auburn No PERIOD  Duke No PERIOD  Florida No PERIOD  Furman

no PERIOD  Georgia No PERIOD  LSU PERIOD Memphis Mississippi North Carolina No PERIOD  Ohio

State Purdue No PERIOD  San Jose State No PERIOD  South Carolina the Swedish

 Tennessee PERIOD In addition  of the teams are among the top  in the

GolfweekSagarin rankings PERIOD

Tennessee will send five individuals out onto the hilly course PERIOD Sophomores

YoungA Yang and Tina Schneeberger and freshmen Erin Simmons and Rosanna

Zernatto will all be playing in their third tournament on the season PERIOD Yang

posted topfive finishes in the teams first two events including

thirdplace at last weekends Tar Heel Invitational PERIOD Schneeberger also

posted a strong performance in North Carolina ending tied fourth in her

best collegiate finish PERIOD Senior Stacey Bergman will round out the Lady Vol

lineup in her return to competitive golf PERIOD After undergoing surgery over the

summer she sat out the first two events of the season PERIOD
